  15 Oct 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +files/odcctools-20070629-solaris.patch, odcctools-20070629-r1.ebuild:
  Marked ~x86-solaris and added patch to allow compilation there. For safety
  the patch is only applied when we're not on Darwin

*odcctools-20070629-r1 (10 Oct 2007)

  10 Oct 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20070629-r1.ebuild:
  Don't install the include files, as they are modified and result in problems
  for packages like tcl

*odcctools-20070629 (30 Jun 2007)

  30 Jun 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +odcctools-20070629.ebuild:
  New 'snapshot' that fixes build issues with tcl, by building the tar with
  --nosdk. Thanks Elias Pipping for testing this snapshot to be sure it
  doesn't cause trouble

*odcctools-20070412 (12 Apr 2007)

  12 Apr 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  -files/odcctools-20070131-darwin8.8.0.patch, -odcctools-20070131.ebuild,
  +odcctools-20070412.ebuild:
  Bump. Not really new sources, but a new generation of the same sources, with
  the latest DevTools, which makes a difference (patch no longer necessary!)

*odcctools-20070131 (31 Jan 2007)

  31 Jan 2007; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  +files/odcctools-20070131-darwin8.8.0.patch, -odcctools-20061118.ebuild,
  +odcctools-20070131.ebuild:
  Add snapshot with patch such that it compiles on PPC Darwin 8.8.0

  10 Dec 2006; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml:
  Add metadata.xml

*odcctools-20061118 (03 Dec 2006)
*odcctools-20060413-r1 (03 Dec 2006)

  03 Dec 2006; Fabian Groffen <grobian@gentoo.org>
  -odcctools-20051031.ebuild, -odcctools-20051106.ebuild,
  -odcctools-20060123.ebuild, -odcctools-20060413.ebuild,
